<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8588&amp;p=165574#p165574"><![CDATA[
A local arcade has a PlayChoice-10 cabinet with Rad Racer, and it exhibits a lot of scanline glitches on the right side of the screen (way more than Nestopia or an ordinary console show). It's not a problem with the hardware, because the owner has another PCB that does the same thing. Both boards also show a single column of flickering pixels on the far right edge of the screen that seems to be related to OAM somehow.<br /><br />I'm really curious as to what timing differences and other quirks the RGB PPU might have compared to the original NTSC model.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=935">BMF54123</a> — Wed Mar 02, 2016 2:46 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
