<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8588&amp;p=165484#p165484"><![CDATA[
I'd suggest to turn off frame-skipping entirely (I actually removed the option altogether from NDX).<br /><br />You can press <strong>Ctrl+F</strong> to enter frame step mode. Then press <strong>Space</strong> to step to the next frame. It's pretty useful for diagnosing stuff like you talked about.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=80">thefox</a> — Mon Feb 29, 2016 11:35 pm</p><hr />
